question: Which is the parent mountain range of "Mount Ayanganna"?
explanation: Mount Ayanganna is a sandstone tepui in the Pakaraima Mountains of western Guyana, northern South America. It is located east of Mount Roraima. With a height of 2,041 metres, it is the easternmost tepui taller than 2,000 metres. It is part of the Guiana Shield and Guayana Highlands.
